article.headline: N.C.-Wilmington 64, Toledo 42
article.story: WILMINGTON, N.C. -- Chad Tomko had 22 points and nine rebounds to lead North Carolina-Wilmington to a 64-42 victory over Toledo on Thursday night. Trevor Deloach added 13 points for the Seahawks (6-6), who had lost two straight games. UNC-Wilmington took control in the first half, taking a 25-12 lead on Tomko's jumper with 4:14 remaining. Deloach followed with a 3-pointer for a 28-12 lead and then hit another one for a 31-14 advantage. The Seahawks extended the margin to 55-29 on Tanner Milson's 3-pointer with 11:54 left in the game. UNC Wilmington finished with 12 3-pointers on 31 attempts (38.7 percent). Tomko made five and Deloach had three. Keith Rendleman added eight points and nine rebounds for the Seahawks. Reese Holliday scored 13 points to lead Toledo (3-10), which had a three-game winning streak snapped. The Rockets shot 12.5 percent from the 3-point line (2 of 16).
